        <h2 class="c-page-title">Automatic critical css with Twig and PHP.</h2>
        <div class="u-flex-set u-flex--align-items-center u-margin-bottom">
            {% include 'includes/sharelinks.twig' %}
            <div class="c-authors">
                <span>Made by</span>
                <a class="c-author" href="https://twitter.com/EpochDC">Jan Decavele</a>
                <a class="c-author" href="https://twitter.com/GijsRoge">Gijs Rogé</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p>Small php library in combination with a twig extension that allows you to annotate above-the-fold-html in your twig files which will than extract all the necessary CSS.</p>
        <p>In combination with loadCSS you can setup a critical CSS solution quite easy.</p>

        <h3>Key features</h3>
        <ul class="c-checklist">
            <li>PHP only, no Node.js required.</li>
            <li>Automatically generated for each page</li>
            <li>Manual control through <code class="language-twig">{{ '{% fold %}{% endfold %}' }}</code> tags</li>
            <li>Dynamically resolves CSS used on each page</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Documentation & Installation</h3>
        <div class="c-block c-block--highlight">
            <div class="u-text-align-center"><a class="c-button c-button--transparent" rel="noopener" target="_blank" href="https://github.com/JanDC/critical-css">Github</a> or
                <a class="c-button c-button--transparent" rel="noopener" target="_blank" href="https://packagist.org/packages/jandc/critical-css">Packagist</a></div>
